    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Other">
        <prj:name>Spectral survey of OMC-2 FIR 4: A laboratory to study early cluster formation</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We propose to carry out, between 85 and 93.6 GHz (Band 3), a spectral line survey of the young protocluster OMC-2 FIR 4, at an angular resolution of 0.5 arcsec. OMC-2 FIR 4 is a prototype source of clustered star formation and also likely a very similar environment to that of the proto-solar nebula. The goal is to resolve and systematically characterise the physics, chemistry, and evolutionary stage of the individual molecular cores and of the shocked regions within this clump where multiple elements typical of clustered star formation are present, including fragmentation, interaction between molecular outflows and external UV radiation fields.</prj:note>
